# std/ui — jobPanel composite pattern (async-job launch/observe)

The pattern extracted from the rozum UCC: registry table (status rows, per-row
✕ close) + instant-POST launch form on a shared refresh tick. This asserts the
tree SHAPE the one call produces — the interactive semantics (instant POST,
status flips) live server-side and in the SPA bridge, already covered by
SpaFormBodyNamedSignalsTest.

[jobPanel](std/ui/patterns.ssc)
[signal, fieldColumn, fetchUrlSignal](std/ui/primitives.ssc)
[text](std/ui/typography.ssc)
[VStackNode, CardNode, DividerNode, HeadingNode, ActionButtonNode, TextNode_](std/ui/nodes.ssc)

```scalascript
val refresh = signal("jpRefresh", 0)
val st      = fetchUrlSignal("jpSt", "/api/status", refresh)

val panel = jobPanel(st, refresh,
  "Jobs", [fieldColumn("id", "id"), fieldColumn("status", "status")], "jobs", "/api/job/stop",
  "New job", text("job-form-here"),
  "🚀 launch", "/api/job/launch", [("kind", "jpKind")])

def kindOf(n: Any): String = n match
  case VStackNode(_, _)          => "vstack"
  case CardNode(_, _, _)         => "card"
  case DividerNode()             => "divider"
  case _                         => "?"

val children = panel match
  case VStackNode(gap, cs) => { println(gap); cs }
  case _                   => []

// list card / divider / launch card
println(children.map(c => kindOf(c)).mkString(","))

// the list card holds exactly the registry table (dataTableView is an opaque
// intrinsic node — asserting its presence, not its internals)
children.head match
  case CardNode(hdr, body, _) =>
    hdr.head match
      case HeadingNode(level, title) => println(level.toString + ":" + title)
      case _                         => println("?")
    println(body.length)
  case _ => println("?")

// the launch card ends in the launch button, form first
children.tail.tail.head match
  case CardNode(hdr, body, _) =>
    hdr.head match
      case HeadingNode(level, title) => println(level.toString + ":" + title)
      case _                         => println("?")
    body.head match
      case VStackNode(gap, inner) => {
        println(gap)
        inner.head match
          case TextNode_(t) => println(t)
          case _            => println("?")
        inner.tail.head match
          case ActionButtonNode(_, label, disabled) => println(label + ":" + disabled.toString)
          case _                                    => println("?")
      }
      case _ => println("?")
  case _ => println("?")
```
